emarks.%20The%20high-value%20targets%20are%20farther%20away%20from%20the%20front%20lines%20than%20they%20used%20to%20be%2C%20making%20it%20imperative%20that%20drones%20have%20the%20reach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFiber-optic%20drones%20are%20regular%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-drone-defense-tech-industry-warfare-russia-attacks-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efirst-person-view%20(FPV)%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20small%2C%20commercially%20available%20quadcopters%20that%20can%20cost%20as%20little%20as%20a%20few%20hundred%20dollars%20and%20carry%20a%20large%20enough%20explosive%20payload%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimages-show-wild-vehicle-cage-armor-for-drones-ukraine-war-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edestroy%20a%20multimillion-dollar%20tank%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20instead%20of%20a%20radio%20frequency%20connection%20between%20the%20drone%20and%20its%20operator%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraines-drone-makers-producing-fiber-optic-weapons-didnt-think-possible-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efiber-optic%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20fitted%20with%20spools%20of%20long%2C%20thin%20cables%20to%20preserve%20a%20steady%20link.%20This%20makes%20them%20practically%20immune%20to%20electronic%20warfare%20tactics%20and%20especially%20dangerous%20in%20combat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20soldiers%2C%20the%20only%20real%20hope%20of%20stopping%20an%20unjammable%20drone%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-soldiers-best-chance-russia-fiber-optic-drones-shotguns-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewith%20a%20shotgun%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There's%20a%20lot%20of%20luck%20in%20that%20kind%20of%20defense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224153%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20FPV%20drone%20controlled%20via%20a%20fiber-optic%20cable%20flies%20during%20Ukrainian%20military%20training%20on%20January%2029%2C%202025%20in%20Kyiv%20Oblast%2C%20Ukraine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689f02c5a17a8c5b4052ed11%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222769%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFiber-optic%20drones%20rely%20on%20thin%20cables%20to%20maintain%20a%20link%20with%20their%20operators%2C%20unlike%20normal%20drones%20that%20use%20radio%20frequency%20connections.%3Cp%3EGlobal%20Images%20Ukraine%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20no%20reliable%20solutions%20to%20defend%20against%20fiber-optic%20drones%2C%20which%20can%20deliver%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-unjammable-fiber-optic-drone-keep-pace-russia-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprecision%20strikes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20are%20emerging%20as%20a%20weapon%20of%20choice%20for%20Ukraine%20and%20Russia.%20Production%20is%20ramping%20up%2C%20and%20cables%20are%C2%A0now%20stretching%20across%20the%20battlefield%2C%20glistening%20in%20the%20sun%20like%20spider%20webs%2C%20as%20combat%20videos%20have%20shown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFold%20is%20one%20of%20many%20Ukrainian%20companies%20working%20on%20fiber-optic%20drones%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-military-training-drone-army-ukraine-germany-2025-8%3Futm_source%3DIterable%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_campaign%3DDefense%2520Flash%2520%25E2%2580%2594%25C2%25A0August%252012%25202025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20country's%20armed%20forces%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20firm%20started%20out%20building%20drones%20with%20a%205-kilometer%20range%2C%20but%20has%20since%20extended%20this%20to%2015%20and%20up%20to%2025%20kilometers%20%E2%80%94%20relatively%20standard%20distances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVolodymyr%20said%20this%20%26quot%3Bfirst%20generation%26quot%3B%20of%20fiber-optic%20drones%20was%20more%20relevant%20last%20year%20when%20enemy%20positions%20were%20closer%2C%20sometimes%20even%20visible%20with%20the%20naked%20eye%2C%20at%20a%20distance%20of%20several%20kilometers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnato-surveillance-jet-saw-russia-air-war-against-ukraine-change-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20front%20lines%20now%20look%20different%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20earlier%20in%20the%20conflict.%20Opposing%20troop%20positions%20have%20moved%20farther%20away%20from%20each%20other%2C%20creating%20a%20large%20gap%20%E2%80%94%20or%20a%20%26quot%3Bgray%20zone%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20that%20serves%20as%20a%20graveyard%20for%20tanks%2C%20armored%20vehicles%2C%20and%20soldiers.%20Important%20and%20expensive%20military%20equipment%20is%20harder%20to%20reach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20flight%20range%20of%2010-15%20kilometers%20is%20often%20insufficient%20to%20destroy%20large%20enemy%20targets%2C%26quot%3B%20Volodymyr%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20fiber-optic%20drones%20able%20to%20fly%20beyond%2030%20kilometers%20are%20more%20relevant%20at%20this%20stage%20in%20the%20war%2C%20and%20Fold%20is%20working%20on%20these%20kinds%20of%20drones%2C%20including%20some%20with%20ranges%20of%2040%20and%2050%20kilometers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227008%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Soldiers%20from%20a%20fiber-optic%20drone%20unit%20of%20the%2093rd%20Brigade%20test%20drones%20before%20heading%20to%20the%20front%20lines%20in%20Donetsk%20Oblast%2C%20Ukraine%2C%20on%20June%2017%2C%202025.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689f0337cfc04e97619b77f6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224672%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFiber-optic%20cables%20are%20very%20thin%20and%20vulnerable%20to%20getting%20tangled.%3Cp%3EJose%20Colon%2FAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESamuel%20Bendett%2C%20a%20drone%20expert%20and%20an%20advisor%20in%20the%20Russia%20studies%20program%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Naval%20Analyses%2C%20a%20US%20research%20institution%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20both%20Russia%20and%20Ukraine%20are%20working%20on%2040-kilometer%20fiber-optic%20spools%2C%20noting%20%26quot%3Bthere%20is%20evidence%20at%20the%20front%20that%20such%20strikes%20are%20already%20taking%20place.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Fold%20is%20aiming%20farther%20than%20this.%20The%20company%20has%20initiated%20the%20research%20and%20development%20process%20of%20a%20second%20generation%20of%20fiber-optic%20drones%2C%20and%20it%20plans%20to%20launch%20drones%20with%20a%20range%20between%2050%20and%20100%20kilometers%20within%20the%20next%20few%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBendett%20said%20%26quot%3Blonger%20distances%20are%20certainly%20achievable%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20they%20will%20depend%20on%20the%20skill%20of%20drone%20pilots%20and%20other%20factors.%20It%20is%20nearly%20certain%2C%20he%20added%2C%20that%20the%20ambitious%20range%20extensions%20will%20come%20with%20considerable%20technical%20and%20environmental%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-working-to-beat-russia-unjammable-fiber-optic-drones-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebiggest%20vulnerabilities%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20fiber-optic%20drones%20is%20their%20cables%2C%20which%20can%20get%20easily%20snagged%20or%20tangled%20on%20the%20battlefield%20%E2%80%94%20either%20through%20enemy%20action%20or%20accident.%20The%20expanded%20ranges%20will%20require%20much%20longer%20coils%20than%20previous%20variants%2C%20potentially%20making%20drones%20more%20susceptible%20to%20hang-ups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20official%20familiar%20with%20warfighting%20innovations%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20who%20spoke%20to%20Business%20Insider%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity%20to%20discuss%20this%20technology%2C%20said%20that%20longer%20cables%20raise%20the%20risk%20that%20the%20drone%20will%20encounter%20more%20obstacles%20on%20its%20path%20that%20could%20damage%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20longer%20cables%20needed%20to%20satisfy%20t