dissatisfaction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20many%20reasons%20why%20I%20felt%20I%20couldn't%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20them%20were%20financial.%20I%20think%20this%20is%20why%20it's%20coming%20up%20again%C2%A0%E2%80%94%C2%A0I%20bet%20it%20happens%20anytime%20when%20the%20job%20market%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-market-power-balance-employers-hiring-promotions-rto-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egets%20tight%3C%2Fa%3E.%20People%20start%20feeling%20they%20can't%20leave%20their%20jobs.%20We%20get%20ourselves%20into%20various%20levels%20of%20financial%20commitments%20and%20mortgages%2C%20and%20we%20start%20to%20feel%20trapped.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-boomers-great-recession-retirement-investment-lessons-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGreat%20Recession%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20in%202007.%20I%20started%20really%20hitting%20it%20maybe%20a%20year%20later%2C%20so%20the%20market%20wasn't%20fully%20recovered.%20That%20played%20a%20part%20in%20it%2C%20certainly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20part%20was%20that%20I%20was%20doing%20an%20MBA%20program%2C%20and%20I%20had%20some%20commitments%20to%20the%20job%20around%20paying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20felt%20a%20fair%20amount%20of%20responsibility%20for%20the%20people%20who%20worked%20for%20me.%20One%20of%20the%20misalignments%20with%20my%20organization%20was%20that%20I%20had%20some%20different%20feelings%20on%20how%20people%20should%20be%20treated.%20I%20felt%20I%20had%20to%20stay%20to%20protect%20those%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20I%20was%20successful%20in%20protecting%20them%20or%20not%2C%20I%20don't%20know.%20But%20I%20did%20feel%20that%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kevin%20Ford%20is%20pictured%20driving%20with%20a%20cat%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689e3ac6a17a8c5b4052e598%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKevin%20Ford%20has%20since%20retired.%3Cp%3EKevin%20Ford%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20starts%20eating%20at%20you.%20Day%20after%20day%2C%20you%20feel%20trapped%20there%2C%20and%20you%20start%20hyper-focusing%20on%20what's%20going%20on%20at%20work%20and%20why%20it's%20not%20going%20the%20way%20you%20need%20it%20to.%20I%20was%20thinking%20about%20it%20all%20the%20time%20and%20have%20flashbacks%20to%20these%20different%20events%20that%20weren't%20happy%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20extremely%20self-destructive%20behavior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20it%20also%20started%20affecting%20my%20work%20performance%2C%20because%20you%20can't%20live%20like%20that.%20It's%20not%20good%20for%20the%20employer%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20good%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20finally%20left%20the%20organization%2C%20which%20took%20about%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESomething%20that%20I%20learned%20at%20my%20MBA%20program%20was%2C%20they%20use%20the%20colloquial%20term%20%26quot%3BF%20You%20Money%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20always%20having%20the%20financial%20wherewithal%20to%20be%20able%20to%20get%20yourself%20out%20of%20a%20bad%20situation.%20But%20we%20know%20that's%20not%20a%20realistic%20expectation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20had%20left%20early%2C%20it%20would've%20been%20much%20healthier%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20It%20was%20probably%2010%20years%20before%20I%20was%20really%20over%20it.%20It%20would've%20been%20a%20fairly%20significant%20cost%20to%20leave%20early%2C%20but%20it%20was%20nothing%20compared%20to%20the%20cost%20of%20staying%20in%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquiet-cracking-leaving-job-personal-essay-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1755338341000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689e3cd7cfc04e97619b709c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C