0product%2C%20septic%20pods%2C%20on%20Amazon%2C%20and%20then%20focused%20on%20getting%20into%20retail%20stores.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20says%20he%20believes%20in%20building%20businesses%20around%20everyday%20products%20that%20solve%20problems.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAlex%20Yale%20does%20more%20than%20%241%20million%20in%20annual%20revenue%20selling%20septic%20pods%20and%20other%20cleaning%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20winding%20career%20path%20that%20began%20in%20consulting%20at%20Deloitte%2C%20featured%20years%20at%20Facebook%2C%20and%20included%20a%20stint%20at%20Amazon%20aggregator%20Thrasio%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-aggregator-thrasio-layoffs-what-happened-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20unicorn-turned-cautionary%20tale%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20eventually%20landed%20him%20in%20the%20business%20of%20cleaning%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Thrasio%2C%20Yale%20managed%20a%20pet%20odor%20eliminator%20brand%20called%20Angry%20Orange.%20Once%20it%20was%20clear%20that%20Thrasio's%20rocketship%20trajectory%20had%20stalled%2C%20Yale%20left%20in%20March%202023%2C%20confident%20that%20he%20had%20the%20skillset%20and%20network%20to%20launch%20a%20business%20of%20his%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20first%20thing%20I%20did%20was%20sit%20down%20with%20these%20suppliers%20that%20I%20had%20built%20a%20really%20good%20relationship%20with%20over%20time%2C%20who%20were%20supplying%20the%20Angry%20Orange%20products%2C%26quot%3B%20Yale%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20He%20was%20particularly%20interested%20in%20the%20products%20that%20used%20bacteria%20and%20enzymes%20to%20clean%20stains%2C%20and%20wondered%20what%20other%20applications%20there%20were.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20did%20a%20bunch%20of%20research%20to%20understand%20what%20types%20of%20consumer%20products%20I%20could%20actually%20adapt%20or%20develop%20with%20these%20enzymes%20and%20bacteria%20in%20mind%2C%20and%20then%20looked%20on%20Amazon%20to%20see%20what%20companies%20were%20doing%20it%20already%20and%20could%20I%20do%20it%20better%2C%20cheaper%2C%20or%20in%20my%20opinion%20with%20better%20packaging%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20product%20he%20launched%20under%20his%20brand%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uncletodds.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUncle%20Todd's%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20a%20package%20of%2012%20septic%20pods.%20He%20started%20on%20Amazon%2C%20which%20is%20%26quot%3Bthe%20place%20where%20I%20can%20launch%20a%20product%20the%20fastest%20and%20with%20the%20least%20amount%20of%20friction%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained.%20But%20his%20intention%20all%20along%20was%20to%20get%20his%20product%20in%20retail%20stores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20focus%20is%20really%20to%20build%20a%20much%20larger%20consumer%20product%20brand%2C%20and%20Amazon%20is%20just%20a%20small%20piece%20of%20that%20puzzle%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20consumable%20and%20cleaning%20products%20in%20my%20category%20are%20still%20purchased%20in%20Walmart%2C%20Target%2C%20Home%20Depot%2C%20Lowe's%2C%20etc.%2C%20and%20so%20I%20think%20it'd%20be%20shortsighted%20just%20to%20look%20at%20the%20opportunity%20size%20from%20a%20digital%2C%20Amazon-type%20of%20marketplace.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223310%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22alex%20yale%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689b7b5fcfc04e97619b459b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222483%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYale%20and%20his%20family%20reside%20in%20Boston.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Alex%20Yale%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22954f65a0-b501-46cb-b2b4-789e255e45f9%5C%22%3EBuilding%20a%20seven-figure%20business%20selling%20everyday%20products%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYale's%20decision%20to%20sell%20septic%20pods%20and%20other%20cleaning%20products%20was%20influenced%20by%20many%20factors.%20One%20was%20his%20connections%20in%20the%20space.%20He%20also%20wanted%20to%20sell%20a%20consumable%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSelling%20a%20one-time%20product%20that%20you%20can't%20get%20repeat%20purchases%20on%20is%20really%20difficult%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained.%20%26quot%3BMy%20hope%20is%20that%20if%20somebody%20buys%20it%20once%2C%20that%20in%20six%20months%20or%2012%20months%20they're%20going%20to%20come%20back%20and%20buy%20it%20again%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20keep%20acquiring%20that%20customer%20every%20single%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20factor%20was%20the%20total%20addressable%20market.%20Yale%20used%20software%20tools%20like%20Helium%2010%20and%20JungleScout%20to%20confirm%20that%20there%20was%20strong%20demand%20for%20his%20type%20of%20product%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20less%20obvious%20component%20of%20his%20product%20selection%20strategy%20is%20leaning%20into%20everyday%2C%20borderline%20boring%20items.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSexy%2C%20fad-driven%20products%20%E2%80%94%20products%20that%20have%20any%20kind%20of%20risk%20of%20technological%20obsolescence%2C%20like%20in%20six%20months%20there%20will%20be%20a%20faster%2C%20cheaper%2C%20lighter%2C%20better%20version%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20sort%20of%20flash%20in%20the%20pan%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20hit%20it%20right%2C%20you%20can%20grow%20your%20brand%20and%20expand%20it%20really%20quickly%20and%20grow%20sales%2C%20but%20they%20burn%20hot%2C%20they%20burn%20bright%2C%20and%20they%20burn%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20playing%20the%20long%20game%20by%20selling%20products%20that%20solve%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223928%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22alex%20yale%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689b7bfecfc04e97619b45c3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222946%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAfter%20launching%20on%20Amazon%2C%20Yale%20turned%20his%20focus%20to%20retail.%20His%20Uncle%20Todd's%20products%20are%20in%20more%20than%203%2C000%20stores.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Alex%20Yale%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20start%20a%20brand%20and%20you're%20chasing%20a%20fad%2C%20you%20might%20have%20a%20couple%20of%20great%20years%2C%20but%20over%20time%2C%20your%20sales%20are%20going%20to%20slide%20with%20the%20fad%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20if%20you're%20looking%20for%20a%20medium-%20or%20long-term%20exit%20from%20a%20brand%2C%20you%20might%20make%20some%20quick%20money%2C%20but%20there's%20not%20going%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20of%20equity%20that%20you're%20building%20into%20a%20brand%20if%20the%20sales%20start%20to%20decline%20after%2012%2C%2018%2C%2024%20months.%20I'm%20trying%20to%20build%20a%20brand%20that%20will%20be%20worth%20quite%20a%20bit%20and%20have%20some%20staying%20power%2C%20and%20I%20feel%20like%20you%20do%20that%20by%20solving%20everyday%20problems%20with%20everyday%20consumers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYale%20did%20seven%20figures%20in%20Amazon%20sales%20alone%20between%20July%202024%20and%20July%202025%2C%20according%20to%20a%20screenshot%20of%20Uncle%20Todd's%20sales%20dashboard%20viewed%20by%20BI.%20His%20products%20are%20in%20more%20than%203%2C000%20retail%20stores%2C%20including%20Walmart%2C%20Home%20Depot%2C%20and%20Piggly%20Wiggly.%20He%20also%20runs%20a%20second%20Amazon%20brand%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.flipitcap.com%2F%3Fsrsltid%3DAfmBOorBK4DhTzT4plBPXCssBue0ghEQPAjXMXvonnOsHSbHIr7lNHq_%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFlip-It!%20Cap%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20he%20acquired%20in%20October%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20more%20than%20just%20product%20selection%20that%20has%20contributed%20to%20his%20business%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20the%20most%20important%20thing%20is%20selling%20a%20good%20product%20at%20a%20good%20price%20point%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20e-comm%20entrepreneurs%20think%20so%20much%20is%2